-- Petrus 2009 Fetches $50,190 as Top Lot at Hart Davis Hart Sale
-- B y   G u y   C o l l i n s
-- 2012-09-19T18:46:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-19/petrus-2009-fetches-50-190-as-top-lot-at-hart-davis-hart-sale.html
A case of Chateau Petrus 2009
fetched $50,190 at Hart Davis Hart’s September wine sale in
 Chicago , with a case of the same producer’s 1982 vintage taking
second slot at $45,410, Hart said in a statement yesterday.  The auction, which took place Sept. 15, was 100 percent
sold and fetched a total of $3.45 million, Hart said. The
third-highest lot was a case of 1982 Chateau Lafite-Rothschild,
which fetched $35,850. All prices are inclusive of a 19.5
percent buyer’s premium.  To contact the reporter on this story:
